    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) Quia fuerunt multe <rs key="#Boundary_disputes">altercationes</rs> inter
                            <rs key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos</rs> domine
                            <persName ref="#people/292"
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Boundary_disputes #Landed_possessions #parentOf #Countess"
                            >Beatricis</persName> et homines domini <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/2151">Petri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Boundary_disputes #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti et Sancti
                            Simeonis</orgName> de <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> que sunt
                        in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2400">insula predicti
                            monasterii</placeName>, iussione predicte domine Beatricis eiusdemque
                            <rs key="#childOf">filie</rs>
                        <persName key="#childOf" ref="#people/125">Matilde</persName>, venit
                            <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Other_clerics"><name
                                ref="Caretus/clericus">Careto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> videre predictas terras unde
                        altercatio erat, cum <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"
                                ><name ref="Azo/venator">Azone</name></persName> venatore, <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Gotebaldus/Teutonico">Gotebaldo Teutonico</name></persName>,
                            <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"
                            ref="#people/2165">Teuzone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldione</rs> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/34">Pigugnaga</placeName> et <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"
                            ref="#people/2166">Gandulfo</persName> gastaldione eiusdem Beatricis,
                        seu <persName key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Judge"><name
                                ref="Maginfredus/iudex">Manfredus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudice</rs>. Ex parte monasterii fuerunt: <persName><name
                                ref="Bernardus/da Burbasso">Bernardus</name></persName> da
                            <placeName ref="#places/482">Burbasso</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus" ref="#people/2164">Albizo</persName>
                        gastaldio de <placeName ref="#places/2923">Casale</placeName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Paulus/de Sustinente">Paulus</name></persName>
                        de <placeName ref="#places/2476">Sustinente</placeName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Turisendus">Turisendus</name></persName>, <persName><name
                                ref="Raginbaldus">Rambaldus</name></persName>, <persName><name
                                ref="Albertus">Albertus</name></persName> atque <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Hugo/clericus">Ugo</name></persName>
                        clericus et alii quamplures. Hi omnes ierunt videre confines unde intencio
                        erat. Tunc ex parte monasterii fuerunt <rs key="#Local_elites"
                            >monstratores</rs>
                        <persName key="#Local_elites #childOf"><name ref="Albertus"
                            >Albertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs>
                        <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Azo">Azonis</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Petrus/Vientio">Petri Vientii</name></persName>. Ex
                        parte <rs key="#Countess">comitissae</rs> fuit <persName key="#Local_elites"
                                ><name ref="Lugarellus">Lugarellus</name></persName>. Isti tres
                        monstraverunt terras et confines. Monstratis terris et confinibus iuraverunt
                        super sancta evangelia in presentia supradictorum hominum, quod temporibus
                        domini <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/1">Bonefatii</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs> sine omni lite et intentione fuerunt
                        cultae et laboratae ac detente ex parte predicti monasterii. Igitur Careto
                        clericus coram omnibus dixit: «Nunc clare patet quia terrae sunt Sancti
                        Benedicti; et ego precipio ex parte dominae meae ut nullus deinceps
                        inquietet predictum monasterium de suprascriptis terris». Actum est hoc in
                        iamdicto monasterio feliciter. Sesto kalendas februarii, anno incarnationis
                        domini nostri Iesu Christi millesimo septuagesimo sesto.</ab>
